    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>After 10 min, remove the chicken tray from the oven and sprinkle over the<strong> grated cheese</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 5 min further or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the cheese has melted – this is your <strong>cheesy BBQ chicken</strong></p>",
